<br>
You are, however, in effect, making a bad situation worse, much worse.<br>
<br>
Bear in mind I have very little direct experience with any of the &quot;Totenreichs.&quot; So, the opinoins and deductions that follow, are based solely on this thread and the events in game that this thread pertain to.<br>
<br>
First, having been caught in a falsehood, that being the &quot;e-mail from Sony,&quot; you posted a retraction in an attempt to indicate that this was supplied to you by someone else who had fabricated it. All well and good, that is possible, but you've failed to consider your audience.<br>
<br>
Many of our members, your audience, were there for that event, and are quite convinced that they saw a ressurection. To post a fraudulent e-mail is only going to further convince them that you have been lying about that event. <br>
<br>
You then propose that you contact Sony yourself to find &quot;proof&quot; yourself, what you should have done in the first place. I can save you the trouble. You won't be believed. People who were disinclined to trust you in the first place have been given ample proof that you are untrustworthy. You could have Abashail himself post logs indicating that events transpired as you maintain, and you wouldn't be believed, until we'd verified his identity, and seen the original logs for ourselves.<br>
<br>
In short, one or all of the &quot;Totenreichs&quot; who you are representing has lied. The fraudulent e-mail makes this very clear. <br>
<br>
You were directed, by your officers to apologize, and have, instead of doing so, made a mockery of one of the conditions of this cease fire.<br>
<br>
At this point, in addition to a sincere apology, which has aproximately zero chance of being accepted, you should be asking yourself what you can do to avoid making this situation any worse than you already have.<br>
<br>
Allow me to advise you in this.<br>
<br>
Arguing particulars, offering posts of &quot;proof&quot; will not facilitate this. Your opinion of what you have done wrong is not relevant.<br>
<br>
What is relevant is what Wudan's officers and AD's officers have agreed to, which is an apology for actions, real or perceived, that occured during the first stages of the war.<br>
<br>
Is your pride worth more than the good of your guild, or this one? Is your pride sufficient reason to contravene the directives of those that lead your guild? Is your arrogance and need to be right of greater value than the rest of the people in your guild that have helped you get to the point you have in the game?<br>
<br>
In short, how selfish are you?<br>
<br>
Apologize or not, make a decision and stick with it, and live with the consequnces. Dragging it out, arguing about how much of an apology you feel like giving dosen't serve anyone, in either guild, at all well.<br>
<br>
Either way, from our perspective, you're simply a problem to be dealt with. How much of one, and to how many people is all that remains to be seen.<br>
<br>
