<br>
I've stayed off the server while Wudan and AD warred except to log in and say howdy once in awhile.  This is for two reasons:<br>
<br>
(1)  Most clerics I group with are in Wudan, AD, or are applying for either, and the war makes them unavailable.  A warrior without a cleric isnt raking in exp, which is my current goal, and<br>
<br>
(2) I like too many people in both guilds to want to get involved, as I inevitably do when I hang around, with wars that I don't even get to start because someone somewhere will say &quot;Rile did this!&quot; or &quot;Rile did that!&quot; even when Rile was just standing around waving his tail.  I figured if I am not on, can't be blamed for squat.<br>
<br>
That stated, and I do remain interested, I read the original post on this thread and some of the replies.  I think some of the replies ignored one sentence in the original post.  That sentence is:<br>
<br>
&quot;This information was obtained by one who question the incident themselves so they contacted Sony&quot;<br>
<br>
This tells me that the person who made the original post was acknowledging that it &quot;was obtained&quot; by someone other than the poster.<br>
<br>
As Neckros pointed out with his 22 inch penis claim, the post would not &quot;prove&quot; anything.  I might add, I would have loved for you guys to chime in while people were busy spewing such &quot;official&quot; crap about me, but remained silent instead.<br>
<br>
However, that doesnt mean that the poster did not believe the email was real.  The poster acknowledged they were from a 3rd party, and did not name that party.  The poster didn't say &quot;I recieved this email direct from Sony.&quot;  If I were to speculate, and I have no idea if this is what occurred or not but is is an example of how it MIGHT have occurred, lets pretend:  A is the poster.  B plays A's character once inawhile.  B sees his friend C's character dead, and so resses C's character at C's request.  B finds out that that was a bad move because that screws A because C is currently persona non gratis to a large portion of the population.  A finds out by D-Z yelling at him about A's character ressing C's character at a given time.  A yells at B.  B says it wasn't him.  B fakes an email and gives to A, A says &quot;Okay, so you didnt do it, I wont beat you to a pulp&quot; or such.  B, the liar in this case, passes off the lie to A without A the wiser.  A then posts the email to show that it wasn't A's char that did the deed.  D-Z point out the email is a fraud, and A is frankly shocked and pissed, and kicks B's arse.  It doesnt excuse the character action, but it does explain the player action. B is the &quot;evildoer&quot;, A was duped.  Of course, it could be that A ressed C.  A simpler explanation, but no more or less probable than any other (see &quot;The Messenger&quot; for other hypos&quot;).<br>
<br>
Some of the replies seemed a bit viscious without making as good a point as either Neckros' or Adell's.  I, for one, was amazed that Neckros had only a 22 inch penis.  I thought his had to be bigger than mine, but it appears not!  (This is obviously a jest, so don't ask for photos please... I don't want your wives all calling me for appointments.  They can have Neckros as a close second <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
This post isn't meant to be for or against anyone, its just one of the observations I tend to make, and thus am sure someone will get pissed at me for making it, probably because it is a dead issue anyway.<br>
<br>
Jon<br>
