Ah, the &quot;little brother/cousin/room-mate/close in-game friend was playing my character&quot; excuse.  Cmon Rile- we've both been on RZ long enough to know that someone else playing your character is no excuse for actions committed by that toon.  The same applies to posting 3rd-party information.  It's the law of common sense- if you post it, you take responsibility for its veracity.  The gist of the tone leads one to believe that the e-mail exonerates him- that clearly isn't the case.  Plus- if any of what was said is true (heh), then there would be no reason whatsoever for him to have been in tactics when his guild was clearly instructed to leave our events alone.  <br>
<br>
The facts are against him- regardless of who was playing him- they are against him, no matter who posted the fabricated e-mail.  Those possibilities change nothing as regards culpability or responsibility- if every such incident could be put down the the infamous RZ little brother syndrome there would never be a case to KOS anyone.  Brothers, sisters, old friends and cousins twice-removed would pop out of the woodwork like nobody's business- messy :P<br>
<br>
