Howdy!<br>
<br>
I never once said the poster was not *responsible* for what the poster posted.<br>
<br>
My intention was to point out that the poster did indicate that the source he was using was a 3rd party, which the poster did not name.  This implies the information is &quot;as is&quot; and generally unreliable, as there is no chain of endorsement to make a judgment about (other than no judgment).<br>
<br>
The other point I tried to make is that we all act upon information *as we know it to be*.  That is, we each make our decisions based on the information we possess and our own judgments of the reliability of that information.  That means, we are perception driven, and anyone can therefore be misled by being supplied bad &quot;facts.&quot;  I provided a stated hypothetical that would provide a good faith belief, even if it was misplaced belief.<br>
<br>
I wasn't making a call one way or the other, again, I just intended to point out that the poster may or may not have had good faith in making that post.  To make a judgment one way or the other in response to the post may or may not be made with good faith either.  <br>
<br>
I didnt say it was warranted or justified, and I didnt say it wasn't.  I just attempted to point out it might have been done in good faith.<br>
<br>
Jon<br>
